Package BSCcore

Interface Summary
Configurable Interface for objects that can configure themselves using a SettingsManager.
FilteredModel This Interface can be implemented by classes calling various database engines.
ModelVisitor This interface defines the methods that a class must implement to be able to use the visitor methods in BSCObject (e.g., visitDescendents()).

TestVisitor A class that implements the ModelVisitor interface, intended for use in writing/running unit tests for the BSCCore code.
VirtuosoBSCFilteredModel VirtuosoBSCFilteredModel filters data from a Virtuoso Database for use within BiSciCol so we can reasonably traverse objects relating to a particular subject.
